&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Design team, you&#39;ll play a critical role in shaping the experience business owners and aspiring entrepreneurs will have when using Durable. You&#39;ll craft beautiful experiences that intelligently and intuitively blend agentic workflows and &quot;traditional&quot; ui.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for designers who want to push technology while deeply empathizing with real customer problems. You&#39;ll work across all teams at Durable to define and deliver what the future of AI UX looks like. You&#39;ll be responsible for execution, holding everyone to a high standard of quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a role where you&#39;ll spend your day in Figma. You&#39;ll be prototyping directly with the latest models, experimenting, learning their capabilities, and uncovering powerful opportunities to push innovative UX to our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of product design experience on shipped B2C products, with a portfolio you can speak to in depth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable producing in code or with AI-assisted coding tools (Cursor, Claude Code, or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent with the current generation of AI creative tooling (image gen, video gen, voice) and opinionated about where they&#39;re useful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing AI or generative experiences: prompt interfaces, automated output, multi-modal interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems thinking: design patterns and component libraries that scaled beyond the features you built them for&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: you have an eye for exceptional brand design and motion and want to help us push the Durable brand further (in product and across marketing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: startup experience or having launched something of your own&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
